<TITLE> Health ministry official shot in broad daylight near police station </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 20 (bdnews24.com)Forty-year-old Fazle Rabbi Munshi, executive engineer of the family planning directorate, was shot by unknown assailants in the capital's busy Tejgaon area, within yards of a police station, on Tuesday morning. Tejgaon police chief Mahbubur Rahman told bdnews24.com that Munshi was on his way to work, when he was shot in front of Imperial Guest House near Tejgaon Police Station at around 9:20am. One of the two men, who waylaid and shot the engineer in the buttock, was caught and arrested by the police. The other escaped. The detained suspect, named 'Rakib', in his early 20s, claimed he and his companion were paid Tk 10,000 to shoot Munshi, the police chief said. The injured engineer was admitted to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. The incident might have occurred in connection with a public tender, police speculated. bdnew
